sfcsSysConfigAdminStatus.name: sfcsSysConfigAdminStatus
sfcsSysConfigAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of the SFCS switching services for this virtual switch. This controls the SFCS state at a chassis level. Regardless of the per-interface state of each SFCS switching element and the state of active connections, writing the value disabled(2) will cause the entire switch to immediately shutdown. enabled(1) -- startup the SFCS disabled(2) -- shutdown the SFCS other(3) -- none of the following

sfcsSysConfigOperStatus.name: sfcsSysConfigOperStatus
sfcsSysConfigOperStatus.description: Indicates the current operating condition of this switch. enabled(1) -- running disabled(2) -- not running other(3) -- none of the following pending-disable(4) -- shut-down in progress pending-enable(5) -- start-up in progress invalid-config(6) -- not running,invalid config

sfcsSysConfigOperTime.name: sfcsSysConfigOperTime
sfcsSysConfigOperTime.description: Indicates the amount of time (# of time ticks) that this switch system has been in its current operational state.

sfcsSysConfigLastChange.name: sfcsSysConfigLastChange
sfcsSysConfigLastChange.description: Indicates the last time a change was made to the configuration entry for this switch.

sfcsSysConfigSwitchCapacity.name: sfcsSysConfigSwitchCapacity
sfcsSysConfigSwitchCapacity.description: Indicates the maximum front panel bandwidth based on current hardware configuration of the switch in Mbps

sfcsSysConfigMaxCnxEntries.name: sfcsSysConfigMaxCnxEntries
sfcsSysConfigMaxCnxEntries.description: Indicates the maximum number of connections which can be established on this switch.

sfcsSysConfigMaxStatEntries.name: sfcsSysConfigMaxStatEntries
sfcsSysConfigMaxStatEntries.description: Indicates the maximum number of stats enabled VCs for this switch.

sfcsSysConfigMaxUpcEntries.name: sfcsSysConfigMaxUpcEntries
sfcsSysConfigMaxUpcEntries.description: Indicates the maximum number of UPC enabled VCs for this switch.

sfcsSysConfigNumberANIMS.name: sfcsSysConfigNumberANIMS
sfcsSysConfigNumberANIMS.description: Indicates the number of ATM Network Inteface Modules currently configured on this switch.

sfcsSysConfigInterfaceCapability.name: sfcsSysConfigInterfaceCapability
sfcsSysConfigInterfaceCapability.description: Indicates the total bandwidth capability(of the engine) for this switch expressed in Mbps.

sfcsSysConfigTypeofSwitch.name: sfcsSysConfigTypeofSwitch
sfcsSysConfigTypeofSwitch.description: Indicates what type of switch this is. other(1) sfcellswitch(2) sfpacketswitch(3)

sfcsSysConfigPolicingSupport.name: sfcsSysConfigPolicingSupport
sfcsSysConfigPolicingSupport.description: Indicates whether or not this switch supports policing. supported(1) not supported(2)

sfcsSysConfigPnniNsapPrefix.name: sfcsSysConfigPnniNsapPrefix
sfcsSysConfigPnniNsapPrefix.description: This is the 13 byte NSAP prefix to use with address registration.

sfcsSysConfigPnniNodeLevel.name: sfcsSysConfigPnniNodeLevel
sfcsSysConfigPnniNodeLevel.description: This is the PNNI node level value. The range can be from 0 to 104.

sfcsSysConfigPnniAddessingMode.name: sfcsSysConfigPnniAddessingMode
sfcsSysConfigPnniAddessingMode.description: This is the PNNI addressing mode - that can range from 0 to 2. 0 - Auto Mode using MAC 1 - Auto Mode using board# 2 - Manual

sfcsSysConfigPnniAddessingAdmnStatus.name: sfcsSysConfigPnniAddessingAdmnStatus
sfcsSysConfigPnniAddessingAdmnStatus.description: This is the PNNI addressing admn status. Down - 2. Up - 1.

sfcsSysConfigFMVer.name: sfcsSysConfigFMVer
sfcsSysConfigFMVer.description: This is the Firmware Revision of the switch.

sfcsSysConfigCTMSlotMask.name: sfcsSysConfigCTMSlotMask
sfcsSysConfigCTMSlotMask.description: This is the slot mask for all ctm boards in the chassis. The least significant bit represents slot 1.

sfcsSysConfigMaxfreecva.name: sfcsSysConfigMaxfreecva
sfcsSysConfigMaxfreecva.description: This is the maximum number of CAC connection blocks that CAC will allow on its free list. The default is 1024. If too low CAC performance will degrade (thrashing control blocks), If too high, memory exhaustion may occur.

sfcsSysConfigUBR.name: sfcsSysConfigUBR
sfcsSysConfigUBR.description: For the set operation: UBR_Cfg is set across all boards in the chassis (that are operational and manageable). For the get operation: UBR_Cfg setting is retrived from the current chassis manager only (one slot only). IF boards are introduced or re-introduced to the chassis their UBR value will be 0. In order to insure a required UBR_Cfg value the set operation should be proformed after slot insertions or re-insertions are completed to the chassis.

sfcsSysStatusTdmCellCount.name: sfcsSysStatusTdmCellCount
sfcsSysStatusTdmCellCount.description: Indicates the total number of cells being transfered across the TDM for the entire switch.

sfcsSysStatusTdmUtilization.name: sfcsSysStatusTdmUtilization
sfcsSysStatusTdmUtilization.description: Indicates the total percentage TDM utilization for the switch.

sfcsSysStatusCurrCnxEntries.name: sfcsSysStatusCurrCnxEntries
sfcsSysStatusCurrCnxEntries.description: Indicates the current number of connection entries for this switch.

sfcsSysStatusCurrUPCEntries.name: sfcsSysStatusCurrUPCEntries
sfcsSysStatusCurrUPCEntries.description: Indicates the current number of UPC entries for this switch.

sfcsSysStatusCurrStatsEntries.name: sfcsSysStatusCurrStatsEntries
sfcsSysStatusCurrStatsEntries.description: Indicates the current number of statistics entries for this switch.

sfcsSysStatusAllocatedBw.name: sfcsSysStatusAllocatedBw
sfcsSysStatusAllocatedBw.description: Indicates the current allocated bandwidth of the switch in bits per second.

sfcsSysConfigAdminReset.name: sfcsSysConfigAdminReset
sfcsSysConfigAdminReset.description: Resets this virtual switch. Writing a value of reset(2) will force a restart of the entire switch, without any graceful shutdown. Any active connections or services will be interrupted. other(1) -- none of the following reset(2) -- force a reset

sfcsSysConfigATOMPersistance.name: sfcsSysConfigATOMPersistance
sfcsSysConfigATOMPersistance.description: This enables or disables ATOM mib persistance. enabled(1) disabled(2)

sfcsSysConfigVcSize.name: sfcsSysConfigVcSize
sfcsSysConfigVcSize.description: This entry is the size of VCs allocated for all VPs in the switch.

sfcsSysConfigPowerUpDiags.name: sfcsSysConfigPowerUpDiags
sfcsSysConfigPowerUpDiags.description: This enables or disables power up diags. enabled(1) disabled(2)

sfcsSysBPClkSelect.name: sfcsSysBPClkSelect
sfcsSysBPClkSelect.description: This enables one of two backplane clocks from any slot. A valid entry is any number that correspond to a slot having a board supporting this mib. A write to this mib will fail if the board with the number selected is deriving its clock from the backplane. A value of 0 indicates that no board is driving the backplane.

sfcsConfigTable.name: sfcsConfigTable
sfcsConfigTable.description: This table contains the configuration and administrative information for each SFCS module. Essentially, a separate SFCS instance exists for each switch module. If SFCS is not configured on a module, than an entry will not exist.

sfcsConfigEntry.name: sfcsConfigEntry
sfcsConfigEntry.description: Each entry specifies the SFCS configuration for the SFCS module.

sfcsConfigSlotIndex.name: sfcsConfigSlotIndex
sfcsConfigSlotIndex.description: The primary index to the SFCS switch table. This identifies the chassis slot number for this switch module.

sfcsConfigAdminStatus.name: sfcsConfigAdminStatus
sfcsConfigAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of the SFCS switching services for this SFCS module. This controls the SFCS state at a module level. Regardless of the per-interface state of each SFCS switching interface and the state of active connections, writing the value disabled(2) will cause the SFCS to immediately shutdown. A gracefull shutdown will be attempted. enabled(1) -- startup the SFCS disabled(2) -- shutdown the SFCS other(3) -- none of the following

sfcsConfigAdminReset.name: sfcsConfigAdminReset
sfcsConfigAdminReset.description: Resets this SFCS module. Writing a value of reset(2) will force a soft restart of the SFCS without any graceful shutdown. Any active connections or services will be interrupted. other(1) -- none of the following reset(2) -- force a reset

sfcsConfigOperStatus.name: sfcsConfigOperStatus
sfcsConfigOperStatus.description: Indicates the current operating condition of the SFCS module. enabled(1) -- running disabled(2) -- not running other(3) -- none of the following pending-disable(4) -- shut-down in progress pending-enable(5) -- start-up in progress invalid-config(6) -- not running,invalid config

sfcsConfigOperTime.name: sfcsConfigOperTime
sfcsConfigOperTime.description: Indicates the amount of time (# of time ticks) that this SFCS module has been in its current operational state.

sfcsConfigLastChange.name: sfcsConfigLastChange
sfcsConfigLastChange.description: Indicates the last time a change was made to the configuration entry for this SFCS switch module.

sfcsConfigVersion.name: sfcsConfigVersion
sfcsConfigVersion.description: Indicates the current revision level of the SFCS MIB for this switch module expressed as an integer.

sfcsConfigMibRev.name: sfcsConfigMibRev
sfcsConfigMibRev.description: Indicates in textual format the current revision level of the Cabletron SFCS MIB for this switch module.

sfcsConfigSwitchHostPort.name: sfcsConfigSwitchHostPort
sfcsConfigSwitchHostPort.description: Indicates the switch port that is attached to the host.

sfcsConfigHostCtrlATMAddr.name: sfcsConfigHostCtrlATMAddr
sfcsConfigHostCtrlATMAddr.description: Indicates the ATM address of the host. (SAR)

sfcsConfigSwitchCapacity.name: sfcsConfigSwitchCapacity
sfcsConfigSwitchCapacity.description: Indicates the front panel bandwidth based on the hardware that is currently installed, in Mbps. (number of ports and the port type)

sfcsConfigMaxCnxEntries.name: sfcsConfigMaxCnxEntries
sfcsConfigMaxCnxEntries.description: Indicates the maximum number of connections which can be established on this switch module.

sfcsConfigMaxStatEntries.name: sfcsConfigMaxStatEntries
sfcsConfigMaxStatEntries.description: Indicates the maximum number of stats enabled VCs for this switch module.

sfcsConfigMaxUpcEntries.name: sfcsConfigMaxUpcEntries
sfcsConfigMaxUpcEntries.description: Indicates the maximum number of UPC enabled VCs for this switch module.

sfcsConfigNumberANIMS.name: sfcsConfigNumberANIMS
sfcsConfigNumberANIMS.description: Indicates the number of ATM Network Inteface Modules currently configured on this switch module.

sfcsConfigBwCapability.name: sfcsConfigBwCapability
sfcsConfigBwCapability.description: Indicates the total bandwidth capability for this switch engine expressed in Mbps.

sfcsConfigMasterClock1Source.name: sfcsConfigMasterClock1Source
sfcsConfigMasterClock1Source.description: Indicates the clocking source for MasterClock1 on each board. The write will fail if it is also currently the source of the backplane. The write will also fail if the board does not support backplane clocking.

sfcsConfigMasterClock2Source.name: sfcsConfigMasterClock2Source
sfcsConfigMasterClock2Source.description: Indicates the clocking source for MasterClock2 on each board. The write will fail if it is also currently the source of the backplane. The write will also fail if the board does not support backplane clocking.

sfcsConfigMasterClock1Standby.name: sfcsConfigMasterClock1Standby
sfcsConfigMasterClock1Standby.description: Indicates the clocking stand-by for MasterClock1 on each board. The write will fail if it is also currently the source of the backplane. The write will also fail if the board does not support backplane clocking. If this value is none(7) and an interrupt on the primary interface for MasterClock1 is received. MasterClock1 will switch to that anims local clock.

sfcsConfigMasterClock2Standby.name: sfcsConfigMasterClock2Standby
sfcsConfigMasterClock2Standby.description: Indicates the clocking stand-by for MasterClock2 on each board. The write will fail if it is also currently the source of the backplane. The write will also fail if the board does not support backplane clocking. If this value is none(7) and an interrupt on the primary interface for MasterClock1 is received. MasterClock1 will switch to that anims local clock.

sfcsStatusTable.name: sfcsStatusTable
sfcsStatusTable.description: This table contains the status information for each SFCS switch module.

sfcsStatusEntry.name: sfcsStatusEntry
sfcsStatusEntry.description: Each entry contains the SFCS statistics for the SFCS instance.

sfcsStatusSlotIndex.name: sfcsStatusSlotIndex
sfcsStatusSlotIndex.description: The primary index to the SFCS switch table. This identifies the chassis slot number for this SFCS module.

sfcsStatusTdmCellCount.name: sfcsStatusTdmCellCount
sfcsStatusTdmCellCount.description: Indicates the total number of cells being transfered across the TDM for this switch module.

sfcsStatusTdmUtilization.name: sfcsStatusTdmUtilization
sfcsStatusTdmUtilization.description: Indicates the percentage TDM utilization for this switch module.

sfcsStatusCurrCnxEntries.name: sfcsStatusCurrCnxEntries
sfcsStatusCurrCnxEntries.description: Indicates the current number of connection entries for this switch module.

sfcsStatusCurrUPCEntries.name: sfcsStatusCurrUPCEntries
sfcsStatusCurrUPCEntries.description: Indicates the current number of UPC entries for this switch module.

sfcsStatusCurrStatsEntries.name: sfcsStatusCurrStatsEntries
sfcsStatusCurrStatsEntries.description: Indicates the current number of statistics entries for this switch module.

sfcsStatusCurrCtmAgent.name: sfcsStatusCurrCtmAgent
sfcsStatusCurrCtmAgent.description: Indicates the current board number of the ctm agent for this switch module.

sfcsUPCTable.name: sfcsUPCTable
sfcsUPCTable.description: This table contains the Usage Parameter Control info for this SFCS module.

sfcsUPCEntry.name: sfcsUPCEntry
sfcsUPCEntry.description: Each entry contains the UPC data for the SFCS instance.

sfcsUPCSlotIndex.name: sfcsUPCSlotIndex
sfcsUPCSlotIndex.description: The primary index to the SFCS switch table. This identifies the slot number for this SFCS module.

sfcsUPCAdminStatus.name: sfcsUPCAdminStatus
sfcsUPCAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of the SFCS module's UPC engine. enabled(1) disabled(2) other(3)

sfcsUPCOperStatus.name: sfcsUPCOperStatus
sfcsUPCOperStatus.description: Indicates the operational state of the SFCS module's UPC engine.

sfcsUPCReset.name: sfcsUPCReset
sfcsUPCReset.description: Resets the UPC engine for this SFCS module. other(1) reset(2)

sfcsUPCOperTime.name: sfcsUPCOperTime
sfcsUPCOperTime.description: Indicates the amount of time (# of time ticks) that the UPC engine has been active for this switch module.

sfcsStatsEngineTable.name: sfcsStatsEngineTable
sfcsStatsEngineTable.description: This table contains information for the Statistics engine for a particular switch module.

sfcsStatsEngineEntry.name: sfcsStatsEngineEntry
sfcsStatsEngineEntry.description: Each entry contains the statistics engine data for the SFCS module.

sfcsStatsEngineSlotIndex.name: sfcsStatsEngineSlotIndex
sfcsStatsEngineSlotIndex.description: The primary index to the SFCS stats engine table. This identifies the chassis slot number for this SFCS module.

sfcsStatsEngineAdminStatus.name: sfcsStatsEngineAdminStatus
sfcsStatsEngineAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of the SFCS switch statistics engine. Writing a value of enabled(1) causes these counters to become active for this SFCS switch instance. Writing a value of disabled(2) causes these counters to become inactive for this SFCS module. enabled(1) disabled(2) other(3)

sfcsStatsEngineOperStatus.name: sfcsStatsEngineOperStatus
sfcsStatsEngineOperStatus.description: Indicates the operational state of the SFCS switch statistics engine for this switch module. enabled(1) disabled(2) other(3)

sfcsStatsEngineReset.name: sfcsStatsEngineReset
sfcsStatsEngineReset.description: Resets the SFCS switch counters for this SFCS module. Writing a value of reset(2) resets the SFCS switch counters to 0 and causes sfcsStatsEngineOperTime to also be reset to 0. other(1) reset(2)

sfcsStatsEngineOperTime.name: sfcsStatsEngineOperTime
sfcsStatsEngineOperTime.description: Indicates the amount of time (# of time ticks) that the SFCS switch statistics have been active for this switch module.

sfcsPacketDiscardEngineTable.name: sfcsPacketDiscardEngineTable
sfcsPacketDiscardEngineTable.description: This table contains information for the Packet Discard engine for a particular switch module.

sfcsPacketDiscardEngineEntry.name: sfcsPacketDiscardEngineEntry
sfcsPacketDiscardEngineEntry.description: Each entry contains the packet discard engine data for the SFCS module.

sfcsPacketDiscardEngineSlotIndex.name: sfcsPacketDiscardEngineSlotIndex
sfcsPacketDiscardEngineSlotIndex.description: The primary index to the SFCS packet discard engine table. This identifies the chassis slot number for this SFCS module.

sfcsPacketDiscardEngineAdminStatus.name: sfcsPacketDiscardEngineAdminStatus
sfcsPacketDiscardEngineAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of the SFCS switch packet discard engine. Writing a value of enabled(1) causes these packet discard registers to become active for this SFCS switch instance. Writing a value of disabled(2) causes these packet discard registers to become inactive for this SFCS module. enabled(1) disabled(2) other(3)

sfcsPacketDiscardEngineOperStatus.name: sfcsPacketDiscardEngineOperStatus
sfcsPacketDiscardEngineOperStatus.description: Indicates the operational state of the SFCS switch packet discard engine for this switch module. enabled(1) disabled(2) other(3)

sfcsPacketDiscardEngineReset.name: sfcsPacketDiscardEngineReset
sfcsPacketDiscardEngineReset.description: Resets the SFCS switch registers for this SFCS module. Writing a value of reset(2) resets the SFCS switch packet discard registers to 0 and causes sfcsPacketDiscardEngineOperTime to also be reset to 0. other(1) reset(2)

sfcsPacketDiscardEngineEPDPercentage.name: sfcsPacketDiscardEngineEPDPercentage
sfcsPacketDiscardEngineEPDPercentage.description: Sets the Early Packet Discard threshold percentage for every port, and every priority on a single blade.

sfcsPacketDiscardEngineOperTime.name: sfcsPacketDiscardEngineOperTime
sfcsPacketDiscardEngineOperTime.description: Indicates the amount of time (# of time ticks) that the SFCS switch packet discard engine has been active for this switch module.

sfcsANIMConfigTable.name: sfcsANIMConfigTable
sfcsANIMConfigTable.description: This table contains the configuration information for each SFCS ANIM instance.

sfcsANIMConfigEntry.name: sfcsANIMConfigEntry
sfcsANIMConfigEntry.description: Each entry contains the SFCS config info for the SFCS instance.

sfcsANIMConfigANIMIndex.name: sfcsANIMConfigANIMIndex
sfcsANIMConfigANIMIndex.description: This index specifies which ANIM we are dealing with. This reference is in the same format as MIB II's InterfaceIndex.

sfcsANIMConfigAdminStatus.name: sfcsANIMConfigAdminStatus
sfcsANIMConfigAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of the SFCS switch ANIM. enabled(1) disabled(2) other(3)

sfcsANIMConfigOperStatus.name: sfcsANIMConfigOperStatus
sfcsANIMConfigOperStatus.description: Indicates the operational state of the SFCS switch ANIM for this SFCS ANIM instance. enabled(1) disabled(2) other(3)

sfcsANIMConfigANIMType.name: sfcsANIMConfigANIMType
sfcsANIMConfigANIMType.description: Indicates the type of physical interface for this ANIM. The types are described in ctron.oids

sfcsANIMConfigNumInterfaces.name: sfcsANIMConfigNumInterfaces
sfcsANIMConfigNumInterfaces.description: Indicates the number of operational interfaces for this ANIM.

sfcsANIMConfigLineRate.name: sfcsANIMConfigLineRate
sfcsANIMConfigLineRate.description: Indicates the line rate per port for this ANIM in Mbps.

sfcsANIMConfigToMB.name: sfcsANIMConfigToMB
sfcsANIMConfigToMB.description: This is the ANIM clock source to board.

sfcsANIMConfigMBClockSelect.name: sfcsANIMConfigMBClockSelect
sfcsANIMConfigMBClockSelect.description: This indicates the ANIM clock source.

sfcsANIMStatsTable.name: sfcsANIMStatsTable
sfcsANIMStatsTable.description: This table contains the statistics information for each SFCS ANIM instance.

sfcsANIMStatsEntry.name: sfcsANIMStatsEntry
sfcsANIMStatsEntry.description: Each entry contains the SFCS statistics for the SFCS instance.

sfcsANIMStatsANIMIndex.name: sfcsANIMStatsANIMIndex
sfcsANIMStatsANIMIndex.description: The primary index which specifies which ANIM instance we are dealing with. This index is formatted like MIB II's Interface Index.

sfcsANIMStatsRxCells.name: sfcsANIMStatsRxCells
sfcsANIMStatsRxCells.description: Indicates the number of cells received from this ANIM's interfaces.

sfcsANIMStatsTxCells.name: sfcsANIMStatsTxCells
sfcsANIMStatsTxCells.description: Indicates the number of cells transmitted from this ANIM's interfaces.

sfcsANIMPicTable.name: sfcsANIMPicTable
sfcsANIMPicTable.description: This table contains the PIC information for each SFCS ANIM instance.

sfcsANIMPicEntry.name: sfcsANIMPicEntry
sfcsANIMPicEntry.description: Each entry contains the SFCS PIC info for the SFCS instance.

sfcsANIMPicSlot.name: sfcsANIMPicSlot
sfcsANIMPicSlot.description: Specific slot which the module that realizes this PIC resides. If the PIC is associated with the chassis and not a specific module then this value will be 0.

sfcsANIMPicIndex.name: sfcsANIMPicIndex
sfcsANIMPicIndex.description: Uniquely identifies the instance of a PIC in a particular slot.

sfcsANIMPicLocation.name: sfcsANIMPicLocation
sfcsANIMPicLocation.description: Defines location of the PIC chip. This takes on any of the encoding values defined below for backplane, module, daughter board, brim.

sfcsANIMPicStatus.name: sfcsANIMPicStatus
sfcsANIMPicStatus.description: Provides the status of the specific PIC chip. the values are defined as follows: other(1) - firmware can not determine status present(2) - PIC seems to be functional notPresent(3) - PIC not found but expected checkSum(4) - A check sum error occured error(5) - An undefined error condition exists. limited(6) - A limited PIC implementation only type code information is present.

sfcsANIMPicVersion.name: sfcsANIMPicVersion
sfcsANIMPicVersion.description: Reflects the version of the PIC implementation that this PIC conforms to. This has the format x.yy . If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

sfcsANIMPicModuleType.name: sfcsANIMPicModuleType
sfcsANIMPicModuleType.description: Defines the standard module type value as defined in ctron-oids.

sfcsANIMPicMfgPN.name: sfcsANIMPicMfgPN
sfcsANIMPicMfgPN.description: Describes the manufacturing level part number of the module associated with this PIC. This information is encoded as follows: 7 Characters Part Number 2 Characters Rework Location. If any field of this object is non-existent, it will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

sfcsANIMPicMfgSN.name: sfcsANIMPicMfgSN
sfcsANIMPicMfgSN.description: Describes the manufacturing level serial number of the module associated with this PIC. This information is encoded as follows: 3 bytes - Date code (year/week) 4 bytes - Serial number 2 bytes - Manufacture location 3 bytes - Board level revision If any field of this object is non-existent, it will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

sfcsANIMPicMfgPartNumb.name: sfcsANIMPicMfgPartNumb
sfcsANIMPicMfgPartNumb.description: This object presents the part number portion of the ctPicMfgPN object. This object contains the same information however in a more human readable format. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

sfcsANIMPicMfgSerialNumb.name: sfcsANIMPicMfgSerialNumb
sfcsANIMPicMfgSerialNumb.description: This object presents the serial number portion of the ctPicMfgSN object. This object contains the same information however in a more human readable format. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

sfcsANIMPicMfgReworkLocation.name: sfcsANIMPicMfgReworkLocation
sfcsANIMPicMfgReworkLocation.description: The 2 character code that defines the location this module was last reworked. This object contains the same information as presented in ctPicMfgPN object however in a more human readable format. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

sfcsANIMPicMfgMfgLocation.name: sfcsANIMPicMfgMfgLocation
sfcsANIMPicMfgMfgLocation.description: The two character code that defines the location this module was manufactured at. This object contains the same information as presented in ctPicMfgSN object however in a more human readable format. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

sfcsANIMPicMfgDateCode.name: sfcsANIMPicMfgDateCode
sfcsANIMPicMfgDateCode.description: The 3 byte date code field when this module was last reworked. This is in year/week format. This object contains the same information as presented in ctPicMfgSN object however in a more human readable format. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

sfcsANIMPicMfgRevisionCode.name: sfcsANIMPicMfgRevisionCode
sfcsANIMPicMfgRevisionCode.description: The 3 character board level revision code field of this module. This object contains the same information as presented in ctPicMfgSN object however in a more human readable format. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks (ascii 32).

sfcsANIMPicTLPN.name: sfcsANIMPicTLPN
sfcsANIMPicTLPN.description: Describes the top level part number of the module associated with this PIC. This information is encoded as follows: 7 Characters Part Number 2 Characters Rework Location. If any field of this object is non-existent, it will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

sfcsANIMPicTLSN.name: sfcsANIMPicTLSN
sfcsANIMPicTLSN.description: Describes the top level serial number of the module associated with this PIC. This information is encoded as follows: 3 bytes - Date code (year/week) 4 bytes - Serial number 2 bytes - Manufacture location 3 bytes - Top level revision If any field of this object is non-existent, it will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

sfcsANIMPicTLPartNumb.name: sfcsANIMPicTLPartNumb
sfcsANIMPicTLPartNumb.description: This object presents the part number portion of the ctPicTLPN object. This object contains the same information however in a more human readable format. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

sfcsANIMPicTLSerialNumb.name: sfcsANIMPicTLSerialNumb
sfcsANIMPicTLSerialNumb.description: This object presents the serial number portion of the ctPicTLSN object. This object contains the same information however in a more human readable format. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

sfcsANIMPicTLReworkLocation.name: sfcsANIMPicTLReworkLocation
sfcsANIMPicTLReworkLocation.description: The 2 character code that defines the location this module was last reworked. This object contains the same information as presented in ctPicTLPN object however in a more human readable format. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

sfcsANIMPicTLMfgLocation.name: sfcsANIMPicTLMfgLocation
sfcsANIMPicTLMfgLocation.description: The two character code that defines the location this module was manufactured at. This object contains the same information as presented in ctPicTLSN object however in a more human readable format. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

sfcsANIMPicTLDateCode.name: sfcsANIMPicTLDateCode
sfcsANIMPicTLDateCode.description: The 3 byte date code field when this module was last reworked. This is in year/week format. This object contains the same information as presented in ctPicTLSN object however in a more human readable format. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

sfcsANIMPicTLRevisionCode.name: sfcsANIMPicTLRevisionCode
sfcsANIMPicTLRevisionCode.description: The 3 character top level revision code field of this module. This object contains the same information as presented in ctPicTLSN object however in a more human readable format. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks (ascii 32).

sfcsANIMPicTLPcbRevision.name: sfcsANIMPicTLPcbRevision
sfcsANIMPicTLPcbRevision.description: Defines the Cabletron revision of the art work for this module. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

sfcsANIMPicMacAddr.name: sfcsANIMPicMacAddr
sfcsANIMPicMacAddr.description: The base MAC address(ethernet format)assigned to the module. If this field is not used then it should have a value of a zero length string. If non-existent, this object will be set to all blanks(ascii 32).

sfcsANIMPicNumbRsvdAddrs.name: sfcsANIMPicNumbRsvdAddrs
sfcsANIMPicNumbRsvdAddrs.description: The number of reserved MAC addresses starting at the address as defined in ctPicMacAddr. If no MAC addresses are reserved this object should have a value of 0.

sfcsANIMPicBoardLevelRevision.name: sfcsANIMPicBoardLevelRevision
sfcsANIMPicBoardLevelRevision.description: Defines the Cabletron board level revision level code for this module. If non-existent, this object will be set to blanks (ascii 32).

sfcsANIMPicModuleTypeString.name: sfcsANIMPicModuleTypeString
sfcsANIMPicModuleTypeString.description: Describes the module associated with this PIC in a human readable format. If non-existent, this object will be set to blanks (ascii 32).

sfcsANIMPicDcDcConverterType.name: sfcsANIMPicDcDcConverterType
sfcsANIMPicDcDcConverterType.description: Describes the voltage of the installed DCDC Converter input and output lines. If the Module does not contain a DCDC Converter this object will be set to blanks (ascii 32).

sfcsANIMPicDcDcConverterInputPower.name: sfcsANIMPicDcDcConverterInputPower
